This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Plea/sentencing hearing on December 12, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

10:08 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Dustin James Drahonovsky in court.  Attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr. in court for Dustin James Drahonovsky.  Prosecuting attorney Jack A. Pitzo in court for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Jensen provides an update; he has received an offer and has discussed it with his client.  Atty. Jensen believes the matter is on a resolution path but wants one more further proceedings to negotiate with the State.  Court recommends setting the matter for plea and sentencing in middle of December.  Atty. Jensen has no objection.  State has no objection.  Court adjourns for projected plea and sentencing.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for December 12, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

11:14 AM; Case called for Arraignment. Attorney Abbey Nickolie in court for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Dustin James Drahonovsky in court.  Attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr. in court for Dustin James Drahonovsky.  Court reviews the case and notes defense filed a De Novo Review of the Motion to Dismiss previously denied by the Court Commissioner.  Court confirms with counsel they want to proceed on the De Novo motion.  Atty. Nickolie provides some procedural history and is asking the court to deny the De Novo Review without oral arguments.  Atty. Jensen responds.  Atty. Nickolie presents additional arguments.  Court places its findings on the record.  For reasons placed on the record the Court denies Defense's Motion for De Novo Review.  Atty. Jensen is prepared to proceed with arraignment. Waive reading of Information. NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED. Atty. Jensen provides an update, he is requesting time to negotiate further with the State.  Atty. Jensen requests a further proceedings date in October.  No objection by the State.  Court adjourns for further proceedings.
Hearing scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Effective August 1, 2022, this case is assigned to Branch 7 Judicial Vacancy, pursuant to 22-SO-04(67).
Notice of Motion and Motion for De Novo Hearing filed by Atty. Jensen. **Reviewed by Judge Lau - This can be addressed at the next hearing date.**

10:17 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Dustin James Drahonovsky in court with attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Nikole Kane appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes that this matter just had the preliminary hearing before the Court Commissioner and inquires how the matters will be proceeding.  Atty. Jensen requests an arraignment date in this matter, and the misdemeanor can tag along with for status.  Court adjourns for arraignment.  Arraignment scheduled for August 22, 2022 at 10:30 am.

09:55 AM Defendant Dustin James Drahonovsky in court with attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court notes that there is a motion to dismissed file by the Defense.
ADA Nickolie states she filed an amened complaint.
Defense acknowledges receipt of amedned complaint and waives reading of amended complaint.
The Court will proceed with the motion.
Attorney Jensen presents arguments and requests to dismiss the complaint.
ADA Nickolie present arugments and requests to deny the Defense's Motion to Dismiss.
Attorney Jense present counter arguments.
The Court places its findings on the record.
The Court denies the Defense's Motion to Dismiss.
De Novo rights given.

Attorney Jensen requests an adjournment of the prelim.
ADA Nickolie objects stating her witness is present.
The Court denies an adjournemnt and will conduct a hearing.

Officer Jarrett Fintel, of the City of Waukesha Police Department, sworn in and testifies on direct by ADA Nickolie.
Cross examination by attorney Jensen.
The witness is excused and the State rests.
The Defense rests with no testimony proffered.
The Court deems testimony closed.

The State moves for bind over.
The Defense presents closing arguments and objects to bind over.
Court finds probable cause to believe that a felony was committed and binds the defendant over for trial.

Waive reading of Information.  
Attorney Jensen requests an arraignment date.
The Court will set the matter over to the Trial Court to track his other file.  Hearing scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Notice of Motion and Motion to Dismiss
Appointing Atty Jeffrey Jensen as counsel for defendant.
Attorney Jeff Jensen, Jr., has been appointed to represent the defendant.
Preliminary hearing on July 18, 2022 at 09:15 am.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.   Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons/firearms/knives.  The Defendant can not go armed with a knife (unless eating or at his place of employment).     Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.   Defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.  Comply with all licensing restrictions.

03:14 PM Defendant Dustin James Drahonovsky in court, in custody, with attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint.  
Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties.
Court advises of right to an attorney.  Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  Attorney Jensen will be appointed.
Attorney Jensen presents an oral motion to dismiss Counts 1 & 3 as probable cause is not found within the four corners of the complaint and presents arguments.
The State presents counter arguments.
For reasons set out on the record, the Court denies the oral motion to dismiss.
Preliminary Hearing requested.  Preliminary time limits waived.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 09:15 am.
Waukesha County Public Safety Assessment Report filed by Wisconsin Community Services.
State's Demand for Discovery and Inspection and Notice of Intent to Use Defendant's Statement and DNA Evidence.
